review_blob: average carbonation, lightly bitter, golden, clear, white foam, caramel, grass,

This the first beer I tried from Renegade and I was looking for a lighter flavor beer to introduce my taste buds to the brewery. There is a light citrus flavor from the orange peel, which is great to get in a beer that is not a wheat beer. It kept me coming back and excited to try their other brews!

If you like coffee, youll love this brew! It has an aroma that teases you, just like coffee. There is also an aftertaste just like that of a cup of black joe. I thought it was great after dinner when people often drink coffee, but without the caffeine!

I loved the fact that this beer was not sweet. I am not in to fruity beers, but this has a more of an earthy flavor. It is dryer on the palate, which keeps it light. It is also a treat to see the beautiful rose color in the glass when served to you.
